    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** - May 24, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🛢️ The Iran deal arrived with missing screws\n\nWashington is selling a near-breakthrough; Tehran is still reading the parts list out loud.\n\n- **The framework:** AP says the U.S. is close to a deal with Iran that would end the war, reopen the Strait of Hormuz and address Tehran's highly enriched uranium stockpile.\n- **The dispute:** regional officials told AP Iran would give up the stockpile later, while Reuters says a senior Iranian source denied any agreement to ship it out.\n- **The meter:** Trump said the U.S. blockade on Iranian ports stays until an agreement is reached, certified and signed.\n\n*Diplomacy has entered the dangerous phase where everyone announces the same deal differently.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/iran-us-war-ceasefire-negotiations-hormuz-e603a7759d6cbd70ce5ed01f439a29dc) | [Reuters via Investing.com](https://www.investing.com/news/economy-news/us-iran-near-deal-to-reopen-strait-of-hormuz-during-ceasefire-extension--axios-4708140)\n\n---\n\n## 🚀 Kyiv got the hypersonic message\n\nThe ceasefire vocabulary is still floating around, but Russia answered the week with missiles and punctuation.\n\n- **The strike:** AP says Russia used an Oreshnik hypersonic ballistic missile in a mass attack on Kyiv, the third reported use of the weapon in the four-year war.\n- **The scale:** Ukraine's Air Force reported 600 strike drones and 90 missiles; air defenses destroyed or jammed 549 drones and 55 missiles.\n- **The toll:** Ukrainian authorities reported at least two killed and 83 wounded, with damage near government offices, homes, schools and a market.\n\n*Peace talks remain available in theory, preferably under air-defense cover.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/russia-ukraine-war-kyiv-missile-drone-attack-998aeaab5833ca397290d9ee2737b0e5) | [Reuters via The Star](https://www.thestar.com.my/news/world/2026/05/24/ukraines-capital-kyiv-hit-by-massive-missile-drone-attack)\n\n---\n\n## ☢️ The nuclear treaty review face-planted again\n\nThe world's main anti-nuclear-weapons forum gathered 191 parties and produced the diplomatic equivalent of a shrug.\n\n- **The failure:** AP says the four-week UN review of the Nuclear Nonproliferation Treaty ended Friday without agreement on even a watered-down final document.\n- **The blocker:** chair Do Hung Viet said no single country blocked consensus, but the draft line that Iran can never seek, develop or acquire nuclear weapons helped sink the talks.\n- **The pattern:** it was the third straight NPT review failure, after Russia blocked the 2022 text over Ukraine and Zaporizhzhia.\n\n*Nothing says strategic stability like failing to agree on the document about strategic stability.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/c500d22a0d91972546acafdfbe358b72) | [Vatican News](https://www.vaticannews.va/en/world/news/2026-05/un-nuclear-nonproliferation-treaty-review-no-agreement.html)"
  }
]
